{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37be-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1503"},"text":"§ 1503.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exclusions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter shall not apply to any provision in a bill, joint resolution, amendment, motion, or conference report before Congress and any provision in a proposed or final Federal regulation that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37bf-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" enforces constitutional rights of individuals;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c0-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establishes or enforces any statutory rights that prohibit discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, handicap, or disability;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c1-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" requires compliance with accounting and auditing procedures with respect to grants or other money or property provided by the Federal Government;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c2-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provides for emergency assistance or relief at the request of any State, local, or tribal government or any official of a State, local, or tribal government;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c3-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is necessary for the national security or the ratification or implementation of international treaty obligations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c4-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the President designates as emergency legislation and that the Congress so designates in statute; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c5-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1503/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" relates to the old-age, survivors, and disability insurance program under title II of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] (including taxes imposed by sections 3101(a) and 3111(a) of title 26 (relating to old-age, survivors, and disability insurance))."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddcde37c6-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/4/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–4, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-03-22"},"text":"Mar. 22, 1995","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/109/49"},"text":"109 Stat. 49","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddcde37c7-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddcde37c8-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddcde37c9-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-03-22"},"text":"Mar. 22, 1995","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/109/48"},"text":"109 Stat. 48","children":[],"tail":", known as the Unfunded Mandates Reform Act of 1995. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s1501"},"text":"section 1501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in par. (7), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Title II of the Act is classified generally to subchapter II (§ 401 et seq.) of chapter 7 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
